@startuml wheel_speed_to_tpms_tire_pressure_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Wheel Speed To TPMS Tire Pressure Signal Flow\n(wheel-speed input -> TPMS tire-pressure publication)

participant "Wheel-speed bus\nFL / FR / RL / RR" as Wheel #F4F7FB
participant "TPMS\ntire-pressure owner" as TPMS #E8F7E8
participant "TPMS state bus" as TireBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\nservice readers" as Obs #E8F0FE

== TPMS Inputs ==

Wheel -> TPMS : frmWheelSpeedMsg\nWheelSpdFL / FR / RL / RR
activate TPMS
TPMS -> TPMS : wheelInputStale =\nethIsRecentTick(gWheelSpeedRxMs, 300)
TPMS -> TPMS : if stale then\nwheel speeds = 0
TPMS -> TPMS : dropFront = (FL + FR > 220) ? 4 : 0
TPMS -> TPMS : dropRear = (RL + RR > 220) ? 4 : 0
TPMS -> TPMS : TirePressFL/FR/RL/RR =\nbase pressure - dynamic drop
note right of TPMS
Representative gating inputs
- WheelSpdFL / WheelSpdFR
- WheelSpdRL / WheelSpdRR
- wheel-speed staleness lease
end note

== TPMS Publish ==

TPMS -> TireBus : frmTirePressureMsg\nTirePressFL / FR / RL / RR
note right of TPMS
Representative outputs
- TirePressFL
- TirePressFR
- TirePressRL
- TirePressRR
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

TireBus -> Obs : tire-pressure visibility /\nservice and observer consumption
deactivate TPMS

note over Wheel, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Wheel-speed samples arrive on frmWheelSpeedMsg
2. TPMS checks the wheel-speed lease window
3. TPMS derives dynamic tire-pressure values from wheel-speed posture
4. TPMS publishes frmTirePressureMsg for observers and service readers
end note

@enduml
